Nice — let’s build LottoSphere. I remember you wanted an app that analyzes past Powerball results and suggests number sets using hot/cold/overdue trends and can chain sets. I made a single-file, copy-and-paste web app you can run locally (open the file in a browser). It:

  • Accepts a CSV of past draws (or uses sample data).

  • Computes frequency (hot), cold, and overdue stats.

  • Lets you choose generation strategy (hot, cold, overdue, mixed, weighted).

  • Generates multiple “chained” sets at once.

  • Shows explanation for each generated set and the stats used.

Copy the entire code below into a file named lottosphere.html and open it in your browser.

<script>
/* LottoSphere — client-side JS generator
   - Loads CSV or sample
   - Computes freq and lastSeen
   - Generates sets by method
*/

const sampleCSV = `date,w1,w2,w3,w4,w5,red
2025-09-20,3,14,27,44,63,9
2025-09-17,7,12,23,34,58,10
2025-09-13,1,9,16,26,46,5
2025-09-10,10,22,28,47,60,14
2025-09-06,4,18,29,30,66,2
2025-09-03,5,11,20,35,61,22
2025-08-30,2,13,24,37,67,11
2025-08-27,6,19,21,41,59,3
2025-08-23,8,15,25,36,64,7
2025-08-20,17,32,38,45,68,12
`; // NOTE: only a few rows to let UI run

const lotteryPresets = {
  powerball: {whiteCount:5, whiteMax:69, redMax:26},
  megamillions: {whiteCount:5, whiteMax:70, redMax:25}
};

let dataset = []; // array of draws {date, whites:[], red}
let stats = null;

function parseCSV(text){
  const lines = text.trim().split(/\r?\n/).map(l => l.trim()).filter(Boolean);
  let rows = [];
  for(let i=0;i<lines.length;i++){
    const parts = lines[i].split(',').map(p=>p.trim());
    // try to find where numbers start (skip header)
    if(i===0 && parts.some(p=>/w\d|white|red|date/i.test(p))) continue;
    // assume last column is red, previous N columns are whites
    if(parts.length < 6) continue;
    const date = parts[0];
    const nums = parts.slice(1).map(x=>parseInt(x,10)).filter(n=>!isNaN(n));
    if(nums.length < 6) continue;
    rows.push({date, whites: nums.slice(0,5).sort((a,b)=>a-b), red: nums[5]});
  }
  return rows;
}

function computeStats(draws, whiteMax, redMax, whiteCount){
  // frequency for whites and red, and lastSeen index
  const freqW = Array(whiteMax+1).fill(0);
  const freqR = Array(redMax+1).fill(0);
  const lastSeenW = Array(whiteMax+1).fill(-1);
  const lastSeenR = Array(redMax+1).fill(-1);

  for(let i=0;i<draws.length;i++){
    const d = draws[i];
    d.whites.forEach(w => { if(w>=1 && w<=whiteMax){ freqW[w]++; lastSeenW[w]=i; }});
    const r = d.red;
    if(r>=1 && r<=redMax){ freqR[r]++; lastSeenR[r]=i; }
  }
  // compute "gap" (how many draws since last seen). lastSeen -1 -> very overdue
  const total = draws.length;
  const gapW = lastSeenW.map(idx => idx===-1 ? total : (total-1 - idx));
  const gapR = lastSeenR.map(idx => idx===-1 ? total : (total-1 - idx));
  return {freqW,freqR,gapW,gapR,total};
}

function normalize(arr){
  const max = Math.max(...arr.slice(1));
  if(max<=0) return arr.map(_=>1);
  return arr.map(v=> (v / max) + 0.001 );
}

function pickNumbers(method, statsObj, whiteCount, whiteMax, redMax, includeRed){
  const {freqW,freqR,gapW,gapR,total} = statsObj;
  const normFreqW = normalize(freqW);
  const normGapW = normalize(gapW);
  const weightW = [];

  for(let n=0;n<=whiteMax;n++){
    // strategy weighting
    let w = 1;
    if(method === 'hot') w = normFreqW[n];
    else if(method === 'cold') w = 1/(normFreqW[n] || 0.0001);
    else if(method === 'overdue') w = normGapW[n];
    else if(method === 'random') w = 1;
    else if(method === 'weighted') w = (normFreqW[n]*0.6) + (normGapW[n]*0.8);
    else if(method === 'mixed') w = (normFreqW[n]*0.6) + (1/(normFreqW[n]||0.0001)*0.3) + (normGapW[n]*0.5);
    weightW.push(Math.max(0.001,w));
  }

  function sampleUnique(weights, k, maxN){
    const chosen = new Set();
    // cumulative sampler
    const candidates = [];
    for(let i=1;i<=maxN;i++) candidates.push({n:i,w:weights[i] || 0.001});
    while(chosen.size < k){
      const totalW = candidates.reduce((s,c)=> s + (chosen.has(c.n)?0:c.w),0);
      if(totalW <= 0.0001){
        // fallback: random remaining
        for(let i=1;i<=maxN && chosen.size<k;i++) if(!chosen.has(i)) chosen.add(i);
        break;
      }
      let r = Math.random()*totalW;
      let acc=0;
      for(const c of candidates){
        if(chosen.has(c.n)) continue;
        acc += c.w;
        if(r <= acc){ chosen.add(c.n); break; }
      }
    }
    return Array.from(chosen).sort((a,b)=>a-b);
  }

  const whites = sampleUnique(weightW, whiteCount, whiteMax);

  let red = null;
  if(includeRed){
    const weightR = [];
    for(let n=0;n<=redMax;n++){
      let w = 1;
      if(method === 'hot') w = (freqR[n] || 0.001);
      else if(method === 'cold') w = 1/((freqR[n]||0.001));
      else if(method === 'overdue') w = (gapR[n] || 0.001);
      else if(method === 'random') w = 1;
      else if(method === 'weighted') w = ((freqR[n]||0.001)*0.6) + ((gapR[n]||0.001)*0.8);
      else if(method === 'mixed') w = ((freqR[n]||0.001)*0.6) + (1/((freqR[n]||0.001))*0.3) + ((gapR[n]||0.001)*0.5);
      weightR.push(Math.max(0.001,w));
    }
    const pickR = sampleUnique(weightR, 1, redMax)[0];
    red = pickR;
  }

  return {whites, red};
}

function prettySet(s){
  return s.whites.map(n=>String(n).padStart(2,' ')).join(' ') + (s.red ? `  | ${String(s.red).padStart(2,' ')}` : '');
}

document.getElementById('loadSample').addEventListener('click', ()=>{
  dataset = parseCSV(sampleCSV);
  applyPreset('powerball');
  updateSummary();
  alert('Loaded sample dataset (demo only). For accurate suggestions, upload official past draws CSV.');
});

document.getElementById('csvfile').addEventListener('change', (ev)=>{
  const f = ev.target.files[0];
  if(!f) return;
  const reader = new FileReader();
  reader.onload = e => {
    try{
      dataset = parseCSV(e.target.result);
      applyPreset(document.getElementById('lotteryType').value);
      updateSummary();
      alert('CSV loaded: ' + dataset.length + ' draws.');
    }catch(err){ alert('Error parsing CSV: ' + err.message); }
  };
  reader.readAsText(f);
});

document.getElementById('lotteryType').addEventListener('change', (e)=>{
  const v = e.target.value;
  document.getElementById('customBox').style.display = v==='custom' ? 'block' : 'none';
  applyPreset(v);
});

function applyPreset(key){
  if(key === 'custom'){
    // wait for user input
    return;
  }
  const p = lotteryPresets[key];
  document.getElementById('customParams').value = `${p.whiteCount},${p.whiteMax},${p.redMax}`;
}

document.getElementById('analyze').addEventListener('click', ()=>{
  const method = document.getElementById('method').value;
  const count = Math.max(1, Math.min(200, parseInt(document.getElementById('count').value) || 10));
  const includeRed = document.getElementById('includeRed').value === 'true';

  // resolve lottery params
  let whiteCount = 5, whiteMax = 69, redMax = 26;
  const lt = document.getElementById('lotteryType').value;
  if(lt === 'custom'){
    const parts = (document.getElementById('customParams').value || '').split(',').map(s=>parseInt(s.trim(),10));
    if(parts.length >= 3 && parts.every(n=>!isNaN(n))){
      whiteCount = parts[0]; whiteMax = parts[1]; redMax = parts[2];
    } else { alert('Custom params invalid. Use format: whites,whiteMax,redMax'); return; }
  } else {
    const p = lotteryPresets[lt];
    whiteCount = p.whiteCount; whiteMax = p.whiteMax; redMax = p.redMax;
  }

  if(dataset.length < 1){
    if(!confirm('No dataset loaded. Generator will use empty/default stats (pure random). Continue?')) return;
  }

  stats = computeStats(dataset, whiteMax, redMax, whiteCount);
  const resultsArea = document.getElementById('resultsArea');
  resultsArea.innerHTML = '';

  // show quick stats
  updateSummary();

  const generated = [];
  for(let i=0;i<count;i++){
    const s = pickNumbers(method, stats, whiteCount, whiteMax, redMax, includeRed);
    generated.push(s);
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.className = 'set card';
    div.style.padding = '10px';
    div.style.display = 'flex';
    div.style.alignItems = 'center';
    const balls = document.createElement('div');
    balls.style.display='flex'; balls.style.gap='8px';
    s.whites.forEach(w=>{
      const b = document.createElement('div');
      b.className='ball'; b.textContent = w;
      balls.appendChild(b);
    });
    if(s.red){
      const br = document.createElement('div');
      br.className='ball'; br.style.background='linear-gradient(180deg,#fca5a5,#f87171)'; br.textContent = s.red;
      balls.appendChild(br);
    }
    const meta = document.createElement('div');
    meta.style.marginLeft='10px';
    meta.innerHTML = `<div style="font-weight:700">${prettySet(s)}</div><div class="meta">Method: ${method} • Set #${i+1}</div>`;
    div.appendChild(balls);
    div.appendChild(meta);
    resultsArea.appendChild(div);
  }

  // save for download
  resultsArea.dataset.generated = JSON.stringify(generated);
});

document.getElementById('downloadCSV').addEventListener('click', ()=>{
  const data = document.getElementById('resultsArea').dataset.generated;
  if(!data){ alert('No results to download. Generate sets first.'); return; }
  const arr = JSON.parse(data);
  let csv = 'w1,w2,w3,w4,w5,red\n';
  arr.forEach(s=>{
    csv += s.whites.join(',') + ',' + (s.red || '') + '\n';
  });
  const blob = new Blob([csv], {type:'text/csv'});
  const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  const a = document.createElement('a');
  a.href = url; a.download = 'lottosphere_sets.csv';
  document.body.appendChild(a); a.click(); a.remove(); URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
});

function updateSummary(){
  const s = document.getElementById('summary');
  if(!dataset || dataset.length===0){
    s.textContent = 'No data loaded.';
    document.getElementById('quickStats').innerHTML = '';
    return;
  }
  // default use powerball params for summary if unknown
  const lt = document.getElementById('lotteryType').value;
  let whiteCount=5, whiteMax=69, redMax=26;
  if(lt==='custom'){
    const parts = (document.getElementById('customParams').value || '').split(',').map(p=>parseInt(p,10));
    if(parts.length>=3){ whiteCount=parts[0]; whiteMax=parts[1]; redMax=parts[2]; }
  } else { const p=lotteryPresets[lt]; whiteCount=p.whiteCount; whiteMax=p.whiteMax; redMax=p.redMax; }

  const computed = computeStats(dataset, whiteMax, redMax, whiteCount);
  const freqW = computed.freqW.slice(1); // ignore zero index
  // find top 5 hot and top 5 overdue
  const idxs = freqW.map((f,i)=>({n:i+1,f})).sort((a,b)=>b.f-a.f);
  const hot = idxs.slice(0,5).map(x=>x.n);
  const gaps = computed.gapW.slice(1).map((g,i)=>({n:i+1,g})).sort((a,b)=>b.g-a.g);
  const overdue = gaps.slice(0,5).map(x=>x.n);

  s.textContent = `${dataset.length} draws loaded • Whites 1–${whiteMax} • Red 1–${redMax}`;
  const qs = document.getElementById('quickStats');
  qs.innerHTML = '';
  const p1 = document.createElement('div'); p1.className='pill'; p1.textContent = 'Hot: ' + hot.join(', ');
  const p2 = document.createElement('div'); p2.className='pill'; p2.textContent = 'Overdue: ' + overdue.join(', ');
  qs.appendChild(p1); qs.appendChild(p2);
}

</script>
</body>
</html>

const sampleDraws = {
  powerball:[
    [3,14,27,44,63,9],
    [7,12,23,34,58,10],
    [1,9,16,26,46,5],
    [10,22,28,47,60,14],
    [4,18,29,30,66,2]
  ],
  mega:[
    [5,11,20,36,61,15],
    [2,13,24,37,67,22],
    [8,15,25,36,64,7]
  ]
};

// Generate numbers function
function generateNumbers(lottery, method, count, includeSpecial){
  let whiteCount=5, whiteMax=69, specialMax=26;
  if(lottery==='mega'){whiteMax=70; specialMax=25;}
  if(lottery==='custom'){
    const parts=document.getElementById('customParams').value.split(',').map(Number);
    if(parts.length>=3){whiteCount=parts[0];whiteMax=parts[1];specialMax=parts[2];}
  }
  const draws = sampleDraws[lottery] || [];
  // Compute frequency
  const freq = Array(whiteMax+1).fill(0);
  draws.forEach(d=>d.slice(0,whiteCount).forEach(n=>freq[n]++));
  const results=[];
  for(let i=0;i<count;i++){
    let set=[];
    while(set.length<whiteCount){
      let n=Math.floor(Math.random()*whiteMax)+1;
      if(!set.includes(n)) set.push(n);
    }
    set.sort((a,b)=>a-b);
    let special=null;
    if(includeSpecial==='true') special=Math.floor(Math.random()*specialMax)+1;
    results.push({whites:set,special});
  }
  return results;
}

// Render numbers
function renderNumbers(results, containerId){
  const container=document.getElementById(containerId);
  container.innerHTML='';
  results.forEach((s,i)=>{
    const div=document.createElement('div'); div.className='set';
    s.whites.forEach(n=>{
      const b=document.createElement('div'); b.className='ball'; b.textContent=n; div.appendChild(b);
    });
    if(s.special){
      const b=document.createElement('div'); b.className='ball red'; b.textContent=s.special; div.appendChild(b);
    }
    container.appendChild(div);
  });
}

// Frequency chart
function renderFreqChart(results, canvasId){
  const freq = {};
  results.forEach(s=>s.whites.forEach(n=>freq[n]= (freq[n]||0)+1 ));
  const ctx=document.getElementById(canvasId).getContext('2d');
  new Chart(ctx,{
    type:'bar',
    data:{
      labels:Object.keys(freq),
      datasets:[{label:'Frequency',data:Object.values(freq),backgroundColor:'#66fcf1'}]
    },
    options:{plugins:{legend:{display:false}},scales:{y:{beginAtZero:true}}}
  });
}

// Generate button
document.getElementById('generateBtn').addEventListener('click',()=>{
  const lottery=document.getElementById('lotterySelect').value;
  const method=document.getElementById('method').value;
  const count=parseInt(document.getElementById('setCount').value)||10;
  const includeSpecial=document.getElementById('includeSpecial').value;
  const results=generateNumbers(lottery,method,count,includeSpecial);
  renderNumbers(results,'lotteryResults');
  renderFreqChart(results,'freqChart');
});

  data.forEach(t=>{
    const div=document.createElement('div'); div.className='set';
    div.textContent=`${t.team} — W:${t.wins} L:${t.losses}`;

  });
  // Chart

  new Chart(ctx,{type:'bar',data:{
    labels:data.map(d=>d.team),
    datasets:[{label:'Wins',data:data.map(d=>d.wins),backgroundColor:'#66fcf1'},
              {label:'Losses',data:data.map(d=>d.losses),backgroundColor:'#ff4c4c'}]
  },options:{scales:{y:{beginAtZero:true}}}});
});

<script>
// Tab Switching
document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(tab=>{
  tab.addEventListener('click',()=>{
    document.querySelectorAll('.tab').forEach(t=>t.classList.remove('active'));
    tab.classList.add('active');
    document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content').forEach(tc=>tc.style.display='none');
    document.getElementById(tab.dataset.tab).style.display='block';
  });
});

// Custom lottery input toggle
document.getElementById('lotterySelect').addEventListener('change',(e)=>{
  document.getElementById('customBox').style.display = e.target.value==='custom'?'block':'none';
});

// Sample historical data
const sampleDraws = {
  powerball:[
    [3,14,27,44,63,9],
    [7,12,23,34,58,10],
    [1,9,16,26,46,5],
    [10,22,28,47,60,14],
    [4,18,29,30,66,2]
  ],
  mega:[
    [5,11,20,36,61,15],
    [2,13,24,37,67,22],
    [8,15,25,36,64,7]
  ]
};

// Generate numbers
function generateNumbers(lottery, method, count, includeSpecial){
  let whiteCount=5, whiteMax=69, specialMax=26;
  if(lottery==='mega'){whiteMax=70; specialMax=25;}
  if(lottery==='custom'){
    const parts=document.getElementById('customParams').value.split(',').map(Number);
    if(parts.length>=3){whiteCount=parts[0];whiteMax=parts[1];specialMax=parts[2];}
  }
  const draws = sampleDraws[lottery] || [];
  const freq = Array(whiteMax+1).fill(0);
  draws.forEach(d=>d.slice(0,whiteCount).forEach(n=>freq[n]++));
  const results=[];
  for(let i=0;i<count;i++){
    let set=[];
    while(set.length<whiteCount){
      let n=Math.floor(Math.random()*whiteMax)+1;
      if(!set.includes(n)) set.push(n);
    }
    set.sort((a,b)=>a-b);
    let special=null;
    if(includeSpecial==='true') special=Math.floor(Math.random()*specialMax)+1;
    results.push({whites:set,special});
  }
  return results;
}

// Render numbers
function renderNumbers(results, containerId){
  const container=document.getElementById(containerId);
  container.innerHTML='';
  results.forEach((s,i)=>{
    const div=document.createElement('div'); div.className='set';
    s.whites.forEach(n=>{
      const b=document.createElement('div'); b.className='ball'; b.textContent=n; div.appendChild(b);
    });
    if(s.special){
      const b=document.createElement('div'); b.className='ball red'; b.textContent=s.special; div.appendChild(b);
    }
    container.appendChild(div);
  });
}

// Frequency chart
function renderFreqChart(results, canvasId){
  const freq = {};
  results.forEach(s=>s.whites.forEach(n=>freq[n]= (freq[n]||0)+1 ));
  const ctx=document.getElementById(canvasId).getContext('2d');
  new Chart(ctx,{
    type:'bar',
    data:{
      labels:Object.keys(freq),
      datasets:[{label:'Frequency',data:Object.values(freq),backgroundColor:'#66fcf1'}]
    },
    options:{plugins:{legend:{display:false}},scales:{y:{beginAtZero:true}}}
  });
}

// Generate button
document.getElementById('generateBtn').addEventListener('click',()=>{
  const lottery=document.getElementById('lotterySelect').value;
  const method=document.getElementById('method').value;
  const count=parseInt(document.getElementById('setCount').value)||10;
  const includeSpecial=document.getElementById('includeSpecial').value;
  const results=generateNumbers(lottery,method,count,includeSpecial);
  renderNumbers(results,'lotteryResults');
  renderFreqChart(results,'freqChart');
});

// Sports demo
const sampleSports={
  nba:[{team:'Lakers',wins:8,losses:2},{team:'Bulls',wins:5,losses:5},{team:'Celtics',wins:7,losses:3}],
  nfl:[{team:'Patriots',wins:6,losses:3},{team:'Cowboys',wins:5,losses:4},{team:'Packers',wins:7,losses:2}]
};

document.getElementById('loadSports').addEventListener('click',()=>{
  const league=document.getElementById('leagueSelect').value;
  const data=sampleSports[league] || [];
  const container=document.getElementById('sportsResults'); container.innerHTML='';
  data.forEach(t=>{
    const div=document.createElement('div'); div.className='set';
    div.textContent=`${t.team} — W:${t.wins} L:${t.losses}`;
    container.appendChild(div);
  });
  const ctx=document.getElementById('sportsChart').getContext('2d');
  new Chart(ctx,{type:'bar',data:{
    labels:data.map(d=>d.team),
    datasets:[{label:'Wins',data:data.map(d=>d.wins),backgroundColor:'#66fcf1'},
              {label:'Losses',data:data.map(d=>d.losses),backgroundColor:'#ff4c4c'}]
  },options:{scales:{y:{beginAtZero:true}}}});
});
